Pork Chops with Rice

None

None::None::Pork chops
0.66::cups::rice
1::package::onion soup
2.5::cups::water

Preheat oven to 375Â°F. Put rice uncooked in bottom of casserole pan. Brown chops in frying pan and place on top of rice. Pour onion soup mix into pan where chops were cooked, keeping juices from chops in pan, and add water. Bring to a boil and pour over chops and bake covered (foil is enough) for 1 hour. Uncover and cook 10 more minutes.
